# ATLASSIAN LINK FORMAT [MUST]

## Rule LINK.0: User-facing URLs — host split

Phoenix wiki and PDT Jira live on **different** Atlassian hosts. Never mix them.

| System | Host | User-facing pattern |
|--------|------|---------------------|
| **Confluence (Phoenix wiki)** | `asterbit.atlassian.net` | `https://asterbit.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/Phoenix/pages/{pageId}/{Title+slug}` |
| **Jira (PDT / oppa-support)** | `oppa-support.atlassian.net` | `https://oppa-support.atlassian.net/browse/{ISSUE_KEY}` |

**Forbidden for Confluence:** `oppa-support.atlassian.net/wiki/...` — returns *null* / broken page in browser.

**Forbidden in deliverables:** REST API URLs (`/rest/api/...`, `/rest/api/3/...`) as the primary link users should click.

---

## Rule LINK.1: Confluence page links (full slug required)

**Preferred format** (markdown):

```markdown
[Page title](https://asterbit.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/Phoenix/pages/{pageId}/{Title+With+Plus+Encoding})
```

**Examples:**

- `https://asterbit.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/Phoenix/pages/72155868/Request+for+disconnection+of+the+power+supply+-+Create`
- `https://asterbit.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/Phoenix/pages/429031426/Request+for+disconnection+liabilities+selecting+logic`

**How to build the slug:**

1. Prefer `webui` from cached Confluence JSON under `Cursor-Project/config/confluence/pages/` — prepend `https://asterbit.atlassian.net/wiki`.
2. Else encode page title: spaces → `+`, `/` → `%2F`, keep `-` and alphanumerics.

**Do not** use page-ID-only URLs (`.../pages/72155868` without slug) in new reports when the slug is known — full slug is the project standard.

---

## Rule LINK.2: Jira ticket links

```markdown
[PDT-2971](https://oppa-support.atlassian.net/browse/PDT-2971)
```

Use `oppa-support.atlassian.net/browse/{KEY}` for PDT and other tickets fetched from that Jira instance.

---

## Rule LINK.3: Where this applies

**MUST** use canonical format in:

- Chat reports (`Cursor-Project/reports/**`)
- Test cases (`Cursor-Project/test_cases/**`)
- Bug validation, HandsOff, and PhoenixExpert deliverables that cite wiki or Jira
- Slack messages that include Confluence/Jira links

Violation is a **MUST** when user-facing Confluence links use `oppa-support` wiki or omit the known full slug.

---

## Rule LINK.4: MCP / REST vs user links

- MCP and REST may use cloud-specific API bases internally.
- When **citing** Confluence in answers, always translate to **LINK.1** asterbit wiki URLs.
- When **citing** Jira, always translate to **LINK.2** browse URLs.
